ORLANDO Pirates have completed the signing of former Bidvest Wits forward Terrence Dzvukamanja. The club confirmed on Wednesday the signing of the Zimbabwean international. Dzvukamanja joins former Bidvest Wits teammates Thulani Hlatshwayo and Deon Hotto who were announced by Pirates on Monday. The 26-year-old has penned a three-year deal with the Rand Stadium-based outfit, who are doing all they can to strengthen their squad to afford coach Josef Zinnbauer a strong arsenal for the 2020-21 season. The club also announced the arrival of Collins Makgaka from Baroka FC on a undisclosed deal. Meanwhile, Makgaka joins the club from Baroka FC. The 24-year old is an exciting attacking midfielder who spent five seasons with Bakgakga.Speaking on his signing Makgaka said: “I am pleased to have joined Orlando Pirates Football Club. I hope to repay the team for the faith that they have shown in me.” ? Welcome to @orlandopirates?? Read the Latest Signings News ???? https://t.co/r51FjGiiZW?????#AbsaPrem pic.twitter.com/Nwm6U2m5jY  